cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.SD, cs.CY 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing and emotion detection in conversations. It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it uses recurrent neural networks for emotion classification. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SD (Sound) as conversations involve audio signals, and cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it has potential applications in understanding consumer feedback and social media threads.
